### @supports

**@supports** applies styles only if the browser supports a specific CSS feature.

---

### Basic Syntax

```css
@supports (display: grid) {
  .container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  }
}
```

---

### Feature Detection

Test for any CSS property+value combination:

```css
/* Grid */
@supports (display: grid) { }

/* Container queries */
@supports (container-type: inline-size) { }

/* Subgrid */
@supports (grid-template-columns: subgrid) { }

/* CSS nesting */
@supports (selector(& > *)) { }

/* New color spaces */
@supports (color: oklch(0% 0 0)) { }

/* Scroll-driven animations */
@supports (animation-timeline: scroll()) { }
```

---

### Not Support

```css
@supports not (display: grid) {
  .container {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
}
```

---

### Logical Operators

```css
/* AND */
@supports (display: grid) and (gap: 10px) {
  .container {
    display: grid;
    gap: 20px;
  }
}

/* OR */
@supports (display: grid) or (display: -ms-grid) {
  .container {
    display: grid;
  }
}

/* Complex */
@supports ((display: grid) and (gap: 10px)) or (display: flex) {
  .container { display: grid; }
}
```

---

### Selector Support

```css
@supports selector(:has(*)) {
  .card:has(.active) {
    border-color: blue;
  }
}

@supports not selector(:focus-visible) {
  a:focus {
    outline: 3px solid blue;
  }
}
```

---

### Progressive Enhancement Pattern

```css
/* Base: works everywhere */
.hero {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 20px;
}

/* Enhancement: only modern browsers */
@supports (aspect-ratio: 1) {
  .hero-image {
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
    object-fit: cover;
  }
}
```

> **Best Practice:** Write base styles for everyone, then use @supports to add enhanced styles. This is called **progressive enhancement**.
